<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="395" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1513,1971]" pageId="6" pageNumber="395">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1729,1755]" pageId="6" pageNumber="395">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species is named after the geographical region of the 
<typeStatus box="[1013,1061,1730,1756]" pageId="6" pageNumber="395">type</typeStatus>
locality, named Planalto Central (noun in apposition).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1513,1971]" pageId="6" pageNumber="395">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,432,1801,1827]" pageId="6" pageNumber="395">Generic placement.</emphasis>
It belongs in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Marx" authorityYear="1883" box="[590,704,1802,1828]" class="Arachnida" family="Araneidae" genus="Ocrepeira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="395" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[590,704,1802,1828]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="395">Ocrepeira</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having wide and low carapace. The abdomen has one pair of anterior tubercles and is attached to the pedicel by its anterior half. The epigynum have a broad scape and is heavily sclerotized, with distinct median and lateral plates. In the males, one macroseta is present on the palpal patella. The large conductor is attached to the thin paramedian apophysis and the median apophysis is long and wide, as stated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Levi, H. W." box="[186,323,1945,1971]" pageId="6" pageNumber="395" pagination="47 - 141" refId="ref6986" refString="Levi, H. W. (1993) The Neotropical orb-weaving spiders of the genera Wixia, Pozonia, and Ocrepeira (Araneae: Araneidae). Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology, 153 (2), 47 - 141." type="journal article" year="1993">Levi (1993)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5824334" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5824334" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5824334/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="396" startId="7.[151,264,1943,1967]" targetBox="[213,1346,210,1904]" targetPageId="7">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1943,2040]" pageId="7" pageNumber="396">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,342,1943,1967]" pageId="7" pageNumber="396">FIGURES 22–29.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Ferreira-Sousa &amp; Motta, 2022" authorityName="Ferreira-Sousa &amp; Motta" authorityYear="2022" box="[349,544,1944,1968]" class="Arachnida" family="Araneidae" genus="Ocrepeira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="396" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="planalto" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[349,544,1944,1968]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="396">Ocrepeira planalto</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[553,611,1944,1968]" pageId="7" pageNumber="396">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[553,611,1944,1968]" pageId="7" pageNumber="396" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
22–25, Epigynum (22, ventral; 23, lateral; 24, posterior; 25, posterior, cleared). 26, Female dorsal habitus. 27, Male palp. 28–29, Male habitus (28, dorsal; 29, lateral). Voucher: 22–24, 26, (DZUB 9280); 25, (DZUB 5357); 27–29, (DZUB 9279). Scale bars: genitalia, 0.25 mm; other drawings, 1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="397" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,150,897]" pageId="8" pageNumber="397">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,150,176]" pageId="8" pageNumber="397">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The females differ from most 
<taxonomicName box="[659,861,151,177]" class="Arachnida" family="Araneidae" genus="Ocrepeira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="8" pageNumber="397" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[659,773,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="397">Ocrepeira</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
by the wide lateral plates of the epigynum touching each other in the posterior view and partially hiding the posterior median plate (
<figureCitation box="[1039,1123,186,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–29" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[213,1346,210,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-21@7.[203,1385,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 22–29. Ocrepeira planalto n. sp. 22–25, Epigynum (22, ventral; 23, lateral; 24, posterior; 25, posterior, cleared). 26, Female dorsal habitus. 27, Male palp. 28–29, Male habitus (28, dorsal; 29, lateral). Voucher: 22–24, 26, (DZUB 9280); 25, (DZUB 5357); 27–29, (DZUB 9279). Scale bars: genitalia, 0.25 mm; other drawings, 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5824334" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5824334/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="397">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authority="Levi" authorityName="Levi" authorityYear="1993" box="[1142,1392,187,213]" class="Arachnida" family="Araneidae" genus="Ocrepeira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="8" pageNumber="397" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pinhal">
<emphasis box="[1142,1335,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="397">Ocrepeira pinhal</emphasis>
Levi
</taxonomicName>
has both the lateral plates touching and triangular scape originating from the base of the epigynum (
<bibRefCitation author="Levi, H. W." box="[1207,1331,223,249]" pageId="8" pageNumber="397" pagination="47 - 141" refId="ref6986" refString="Levi, H. W. (1993) The Neotropical orb-weaving spiders of the genera Wixia, Pozonia, and Ocrepeira (Araneae: Araneidae). Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology, 153 (2), 47 - 141." type="journal article" year="1993">Levi, 1993</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 213) as in 
<taxonomicName authority="Ferreira-Sousa &amp; Motta, 2022" authorityName="Ferreira-Sousa &amp; Motta" authorityYear="2022" box="[212,341,259,285]" class="Arachnida" family="Araneidae" genus="Ocrepeira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="8" pageNumber="397" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="planalto" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[212,341,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="397">O. planalto</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[349,413,259,285]" pageId="8" pageNumber="397">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[349,413,259,285]" pageId="8" pageNumber="397" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
The latter is different by having the scape slightly smaller than the base (
<figureCitation box="[1248,1332,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–29" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[213,1346,210,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-21@7.[203,1385,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 22–29. Ocrepeira planalto n. sp. 22–25, Epigynum (22, ventral; 23, lateral; 24, posterior; 25, posterior, cleared). 26, Female dorsal habitus. 27, Male palp. 28–29, Male habitus (28, dorsal; 29, lateral). Voucher: 22–24, 26, (DZUB 9280); 25, (DZUB 5357); 27–29, (DZUB 9279). Scale bars: genitalia, 0.25 mm; other drawings, 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5824334" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5824334/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="397">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
), and the epigynum is about square-shaped in posterior view due to its very wide lateral plates (
<figureCitation box="[1133,1218,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–29" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[213,1346,210,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-21@7.[203,1385,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 22–29. Ocrepeira planalto n. sp. 22–25, Epigynum (22, ventral; 23, lateral; 24, posterior; 25, posterior, cleared). 26, Female dorsal habitus. 27, Male palp. 28–29, Male habitus (28, dorsal; 29, lateral). Voucher: 22–24, 26, (DZUB 9280); 25, (DZUB 5357); 27–29, (DZUB 9279). Scale bars: genitalia, 0.25 mm; other drawings, 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5824334" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5824334/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="397">Fig. 24</figureCitation>
). Furthermore, two dark spots are present in the ventral view of the epigynum in all females of 
<taxonomicName authority="Ferreira-Sousa &amp; Motta, 2022" authorityName="Ferreira-Sousa &amp; Motta" authorityYear="2022" box="[1009,1137,331,357]" class="Arachnida" family="Araneidae" genus="Ocrepeira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="8" pageNumber="397" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="planalto" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[1009,1137,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="397">O. planalto</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1145,1209,331,357]" pageId="8" pageNumber="397">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1145,1209,331,357]" pageId="8" pageNumber="397" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1226,1311,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–29" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[213,1346,210,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-21@7.[203,1385,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 22–29. Ocrepeira planalto n. sp. 22–25, Epigynum (22, ventral; 23, lateral; 24, posterior; 25, posterior, cleared). 26, Female dorsal habitus. 27, Male palp. 28–29, Male habitus (28, dorsal; 29, lateral). Voucher: 22–24, 26, (DZUB 9280); 25, (DZUB 5357); 27–29, (DZUB 9279). Scale bars: genitalia, 0.25 mm; other drawings, 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5824334" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5824334/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="397">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
). The male resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Levi" authorityName="Levi" authorityYear="1993" box="[270,418,367,393]" class="Arachnida" family="Araneidae" genus="Ocrepeira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="8" pageNumber="397" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gima">
<emphasis box="[270,360,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="397">O. gima</emphasis>
Levi
</taxonomicName>
by the sickle-shaped terminal apophysis and the size of the median apophysis. It differs by the elliptical shape of the conductor. Both terminal and median apophysis are longer and the latter has a smooth tip (
<figureCitation box="[160,244,439,465]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–29" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[213,1346,210,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-21@7.[203,1385,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 22–29. Ocrepeira planalto n. sp. 22–25, Epigynum (22, ventral; 23, lateral; 24, posterior; 25, posterior, cleared). 26, Female dorsal habitus. 27, Male palp. 28–29, Male habitus (28, dorsal; 29, lateral). Voucher: 22–24, 26, (DZUB 9280); 25, (DZUB 5357); 27–29, (DZUB 9279). Scale bars: genitalia, 0.25 mm; other drawings, 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5824334" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5824334/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="397">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="398" pageId="8" pageNumber="397" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,150,897]" pageId="8" pageNumber="397">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,474,500]" pageId="8" pageNumber="397">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[355,966,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="397">
Female 
<typeStatus box="[449,545,475,501]" pageId="8" pageNumber="397">holotype</typeStatus>
from Fazenda Trijunção, Jaborandi
</emphasis>
. Total length 6.40. Carapace: 3.05 long, 2.68 wide, 1.18 high. Cephalic region brown with short white setae, thoracic region with glabrous dark brown sides. Clypeus: 0.21. Chelicerae: orange to brown, fangs redish-brown. Eye diameters: AME 0.14, ALE 0.11, PME 0.16, PLE 0.10. Eye interdistances: AME–AME 0.18, AME–ALE 0.53, PME–PME 0.25, PME–PLE 0.67, AME–PME 0.15. Endites: 0.54 long, 0.46 wide, brown, white from the half to median edges. Labium: 0.45 long, 0.64 wide, same color pattern as in endites. Sternum: 1.30 long, 1.34 wide, orange with white spots. Legs: yellow with irregular brown rings and spots. Leg formula 1 2 4 3. Measures: L1. Femur 3.27, patella 1.44, tibia 2.48, metatarsus 2.32, tarsus 0.90 / L2. Femur 2.93, patella 1.43, tibia 2.07, metatarsus 2.16, tarsus 0.78 / L3. Femur 1.73, patella 0.94, tibia 1.25, metatarsus 1.13, tarsus 0.63 / L4. Femur 2.57, patella 1.05, tibia 1.90, metatarsus 1.95, tarsus 0.68 / Pedipalp. Femur 0.75, patella 0.40, tibia 0.54, tarsus 0.93. Abdomen: 5.57 long, 3.93 wide, 2.67 high. Dark grey with light spots and a white cardiac mark, the sides have a wavy black line each. The venter has a wide dark grey area, with two small white spots near the spinnerets.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5824338" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5824338" box="[151,1315,1792,1816]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5824338/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="397" startId="8.[151,250,1792,1816]" targetBox="[151,1436,921,1768]" targetPageId="8">
